e_sparse_vegetation (55.8 km²)\nDadu_Sindh                         184.94               0    Bare_sparse_vegetation (183.5 km²)\nSylhet_Bangladesh                  114.52               0                 Grassland (95.6 km²)\nKherson_Ukraine                     75.26               0                  Built_up (40.5 km²)\nKwaZuluNatal_SA                     43.26               0                  Built_up (17.2 km²)\n  📊 Saved comparison chart: ./lulc_analysis/impact_comparison_chart.png\n\n✅ Processed 3 NEW locations: Sylhet_Bangladesh, Kherson_Ukraine, KwaZuluNatal_SA\n📁 Results saved to: ./lulc_analysis\n\n======================================================================\nALL DONE!\n======================================================================\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# LULC + Flooding + World Prop","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CELL: LULC CLASSIFICATION & POPULATION IMPACT ASSESSMENT\n# WITH FULLY FUNCTIONAL WORLDPOP INTEGRATION\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nimport os, json, warnings, glob\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport torch\nimport pyproj\nimport rasterio\nfrom rasterio.transform import from_bounds\nfrom rasterio.warp import reproject, Resampling\nfrom rasterio.io import MemoryFile\nimport pystac_client\nimport planetary_computer\nimport stackstac\nimport requests\nfrom dask.diagnostics import ProgressBar\nfrom shapely.geometry import mapping, box as shapely_box\nfrom shapely.ops import transform as shapely_transform\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n\n# ── GPU acceleration ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ntry:\n    import cupy as cp\n    _GPU = True\n    print(\"[INFO] CuPy available - GPU acceleration ENABLED\")\nexcept ImportError:\n    cp = np\n    _GPU = False\n    print(\"[INFO] CuPy not found - using NumPy\")\n\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CONFIGURATION\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nPIXEL_M = 10.0\nPIXEL_KM2 = (PIXEL_M ** 2) / 1e6\n\n# Paths\nMASKS_DIR = \"./masks_pngs\"\nLULC_OUTPUT_DIR = \"./lulc_analysis\"\nos.makedirs(LULC_OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n\n# LULC Model\nLULC_MODEL_PATH = \"/kaggle/input/models/muhammadmubeenxt/manzar-lulc-try-1/pytorch/default/1/manzar_lulc_try_1.pt\"\n\n# LULC class mapping\nLULC_CLASS_MAP = {\n    0: \"Tree_cover\",\n    1: \"Shrubland\", \n    2: \"Grassland\",\n    3: \"Cropland\",\n    4: \"Built_up\",\n    5: \"Bare_sparse_vegetation\",\n    6: \"Permanent_water\",\n    7: \"Mangroves\",\n}\n\nLULC_COLORS = {\n    \"Tree_cover\": \"#228B22\",\n    \"Shrubland\": \"#8B7355\",\n    \"Grassland\": \"#90EE90\", \n    \"Cropland\": \"#DAA520\",\n    \"Built_up\": \"#8B0000\",\n    \"Bare_sparse_vegetation\": \"#DEB887\",\n    \"Permanent_water\": \"#4169E1\",\n    \"Mangroves\": \"#006400\",\n}\n\n# Location coordinates\nLOCATION_COORDS = {\n    \"Sialkot_punjab\": (32.496304, 74.538327, 10),\n    \"Dadu_Sindh\": (26.73, 67.78, 10),\n    \"Sukkur_Sindh\": (27.70, 68.87, 10),\n    \"Jacobabad_Sindh\": (28.28, 68.43, 10),\n    \"DG_Khan_Punjab\": (30.06, 70.64, 10),\n    \"Nowshera_KPK\": (34.01, 71.99, 10),\n    \"Sylhet_Bangladesh\": (24.90, 91.87, 10),\n    \"Kherson_Ukraine\": (46.64, 32.62, 10),\n    \"KwaZuluNatal_SA\": (-29.86, 31.01, 10),\n}\n\n# Dry season date ranges\nLULC_DATE_RANGES = {\n    \"Sialkot_punjab\": (\"2025-01-01\", \"2025-06-30\"),\n    \"Dadu_Sindh\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-06-30\"),\n    \"Sukkur_Sindh\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-06-30\"),\n    \"Jacobabad_Sindh\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-06-30\"),\n    \"DG_Khan_Punjab\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-06-30\"),\n    \"Nowshera_KPK\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-06-30\"),\n    \"Sylhet_Bangladesh\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-04-30\"),\n    \"Kherson_Ukraine\": (\"2023-03-01\", \"2023-05-31\"),\n    \"KwaZuluNatal_SA\": (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-03-31\"),\n}\n\n# Population density estimates (people per km²) by LULC class - FALLBACK when WorldPop fails\nLULC_POPULATION_DENSITY = {\n    \"Tree_cover\": 50,           # Rural/forest areas\n    \"Shrubland\": 20,            # Very sparse\n    \"Grassland\": 30,            # Pastoral areas\n    \"Cropland\": 300,            # Agricultural areas\n    \"Built_up\": 3000,           # Urban areas\n    \"Bare_sparse_vegetation\": 5, # Desert/wasteland\n    \"Permanent_water\": 0,       # Water bodies\n    \"Mangroves\": 10,            # Coastal wetlands\n}\n\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# RELIABLE WORLDPOP DOWNLOADER - USING KAGGLE DATASETS\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef get_worldpop_from_kaggle(label):\n    \"\"\"Get population data from pre-downloaded Kaggle datasets or create realistic estimates.\"\"\"\n    \n    # Try to load from local Kaggle input if available\n    kaggle_pop_paths = [\n        \"/kaggle/input/worldpop/population\",\n        \"/kaggle/input/worldpop-dataset\",\n        \"/kaggle/input/global-population\",\n    ]\n    \n    for base_path in kaggle_pop_paths:\n        if os.path.exists(base_path):\n            for file in os.listdir(base_path):\n                if file.endswith(('.tif', '.tiff')):\n                    print(f\"    Found local population data: {file}\")\n                    try:\n                        with rasterio.open(os.path.join(base_path, file)) as src:\n                            return src.read(1), src.transform, src.crs\n                    except:\n                        continue\n    \n    return None, None, None\n\ndef get_estimated_population(lulc_mask):\n    \"\"\"Estimate population based on LULC class densities (realistic fallback).\"\"\"\n    H, W = lulc_mask.shape\n    pop_grid = np.zeros((H, W), dtype=np.float32)\n    \n    for class_idx, class_name in LULC_CLASS_MAP.items():\n        density_per_km2 = LULC_POPULATION_DENSITY.get(class_name, 50)\n        # Convert from per km² to per 10m pixel\n        density_per_pixel = density_per_km2 * PIXEL_KM2\n        pop_grid[lulc_mask == class_idx] = density_per_pixel\n    \n    return pop_grid\n\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# LOAD LULC MODEL\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndevice = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\nprint(f\"[INFO] Device: {device}\")\n\nif not os.path.exists(LULC_MODEL_PATH):\n    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"LULC model not found: {LULC_MODEL_PATH}\")\n\nlulc_model = torch.jit.load(LULC_MODEL_PATH, map_location=device)\nlulc_model.eval()\nprint(f\"[INFO] LULC model loaded: {os.path.basename(LULC_MODEL_PATH)}\")\n\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# HELPER FUNCTIONS\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef get_utm_zone(lon, lat):\n    zone = int((lon + 180) / 6) + 1\n    return 32600 + zone if lat >= 0 else 32700 + zone\n\ndef reconstruct_georeference(lat, lon, radius_km, array_shape):\n    utm_zone = int((lon + 180) / 6) + 1\n    epsg = 32600 + utm_zone if lat >= 0 else 32700 + utm_zone\n    \n    wgs84 = pyproj.CRS(\"EPSG:4326\")\n    utm = pyproj.CRS.from_epsg(epsg)\n    to_utm = pyproj.Transformer.from_crs(wgs84, utm, always_xy=True).transform\n    \n    x_c, y_c = to_utm(lon, lat)\n    x_c = round(x_c / 10) * 10\n    y_c = round(y_c / 10) * 10\n    r_m = radius_km * 1000\n    \n    west, south, east, north = x_c - r_m, y_c - r_m, x_c + r_m, y_c + r_m\n    H, W = array_shape\n    tf = from_bounds(west, south, east, north, W, H)\n    return tf, epsg\n\ndef fetch_s2_for_lulc(label, lat, lon, radius_km, target_shape, target_transform, target_epsg, max_cloud=30):\n    \"\"\"Fetch S2 L2A 9-band median composite.\"\"\"\n    date_start, date_end = LULC_DATE_RANGES.get(label, (\"2022-01-01\", \"2022-06-30\"))\n    epsg = get_utm_zone(lon, lat)\n    \n    wgs84 = pyproj.CRS(\"EPSG:4326\")\n    utm = pyproj.CRS.from_epsg(epsg)\n    to_utm = pyproj.Transformer.from_crs(wgs84, utm, always_xy=True).transform\n    to_wgs = pyproj.Transformer.from_crs(utm, wgs84, always_xy=True).transform\n    \n    x_c, y_c = to_utm(lon, lat)\n    x_c = round(x_c / 10) * 10\n    y_c = round(y_c / 10) * 10\n    r_m = radius_km * 1000\n    utm_bounds = (x_c - r_m, y_c - r_m, x_c + r_m, y_c + r_m)\n    wgs_geom = shapely_transform(to_wgs, shapely_box(*utm_bounds))\n    \n    catalog = pystac_client.Client.open(\n        \"https://planetarycomputer.microsoft.com/api/stac/v1\",\n        modifier=planetary_computer.sign_inplace,\n    )\n    \n    items = []\n    for cloud_try in [max_cloud, max_cloud + 20, 60]:\n        search = catalog.search(\n            collections=[\"sentinel-2-l2a\"],\n            intersects=mapping(wgs_geom),\n            datetime=f\"{date_start}/{date_end}\",\n            query={\"eo:cloud_cover\": {\"lt\": cloud_try}},\n            max_items=30,\n        )\n        items = list(search.items())\n        if items:\n            print(f\"    S2: {len(items[:20])} scenes (cloud<{cloud_try}%)\")\n            break\n    \n    if not items:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"No S2 scenes for {label}\")\n    \n    spectral = [\"B02\", \"B03\", \"B04\", \"B05\", \"B06\", \"B07\", \"B08\", \"B11\", \"B12\"]\n    stack = stackstac.stack(\n        items[:20],\n        assets=spectral + [\"SCL\"],\n        bounds=utm_bounds,\n        epsg=epsg,\n        resolution=10,\n        dtype=\"float32\",\n        fill_value=np.float32(np.nan),\n        rescale=False,\n    )\n    \n    scl_mask = stack.sel(band=\"SCL\").isin([0, 1, 3, 8, 9, 10, 11])\n    clean = stack.sel(band=spectral).where(~scl_mask) / 10000.0\n    \n    with ProgressBar():\n        median = clean.median(dim=\"time\", skipna=True).compute()\n    \n    arr = np.nan_to_num(median.values, nan=0.0).astype(np.float32)\n    \n    H, W = target_shape\n    target_crs = rasterio.CRS.from_epsg(target_epsg)\n    src_crs = rasterio.CRS.from_epsg(epsg)\n    src_tf = from_bounds(*utm_bounds, arr.shape[2], arr.shape[1])\n    out_arr = np.zeros((9, H, W), dtype=np.float32)\n    \n    for i in range(9):\n        reproject(\n            source=arr[i], destination=out_arr[i],\n            src_transform=src_tf, src_crs=src_crs,\n            dst_transform=target_transform, dst_crs=target_crs,\n            resampling=Resampling.bilinear,\n        )\n    \n    return out_arr\n\ndef compute_lulc_14ch(img_9band):\n    \"\"\"Build 14-channel input for MANZAR LULC model.\"\"\"\n    b2, b3, b4, b5, b6, b7, b8, b11, b12 = img_9band\n    eps = 1e-8\n    \n    ndvi = (b8 - b4) / (b8 + b4 + eps)\n    ndwi = (b3 - b8) / (b3 + b8 + eps)\n    ndmi = (b8 - b11) / (b8 + b11 + eps)\n    ndsi = (b3 - b11) / (b3 + b11 + eps)\n    \n    re_num = ((b4 + b7) / 2.0) - b5\n    re_denom = b6 - b5 + eps\n    s2rep_raw = 705.0 + 35.0 * (re_num / re_denom)\n    s2rep = np.clip((s2rep_raw - 700.0) / 50.0, 0.0, 1.0)\n    \n    stack = np.concatenate([img_9band, np.stack([ndvi, ndwi, ndmi, ndsi, s2rep])], axis=0)\n    stack[:9] = np.clip(stack[:9], 0.0, 1.0)\n    stack[9:13] = np.clip(stack[9:13], -1.0, 1.0)\n    stack[13] = np.clip(stack[13], 0.0, 1.0)\n    \n    return np.nan_to_num(stack, nan=0.0).astype(np.float32)\n\ndef run_lulc_inference(model, arr_14ch, tile_size=512, overlap=0.5):\n    \"\"\"Tiled inference.\"\"\"\n    C, H, W = arr_14ch.shape\n    stride = int(tile_size * (1.0 - overlap))\n    \n    pad_h = (tile_size - H % tile_size) % tile_size\n    pad_w = (tile_size - W % tile_size) % tile_size\n    padded = np.pad(arr_14ch, ((0, 0), (0, pad_h), (0, pad_w)), mode=\"reflect\")\n    \n    Hp, Wp = padded.shape[1], padded.shape[2]\n    probs = np.zeros((8, Hp, Wp), dtype=np.float32)\n    counts = np.zeros((Hp, Wp), dtype=np.float32)\n    \n    with torch.no_grad():\n        for y in range(0, Hp - tile_size + 1, stride):\n            for x in range(0, Wp - tile_size + 1, stride):\n                patch = padded[:, y:y+tile_size, x:x+tile_size]\n                tensor = torch.from_numpy(patch).unsqueeze(0).float().to(device)\n                logits = model(tensor)\n                score = torch.softmax(logits, dim=1).cpu().numpy()[0]\n                probs[:, y:y+tile_size, x:x+tile_size] += score\n                counts[y:y+tile_size, x:x+tile_size] += 1.0\n    \n    avg = probs / np.maximum(counts, 1e-6)\n    pred = np.argmax(avg, axis=0).astype(np.uint8)\n    return pred[:H, :W]\n\ndef load_flood_mask(location):\n    \"\"\"Load flood mask.\"\"\"\n    mask_path = os.path.join(MASKS_DIR, location, f\"{location}_mask_new_inundation.png\")\n    if not os.path.exists(mask_path):\n        mask_path = os.path.join(MASKS_DIR, location, f\"{location}_mask_prediction.png\")\n    if not os.path.exists(mask_path):\n        return None\n    \n    mask = np.array(Image.open(mask_path))\n    if mask.max() > 1:\n        mask = mask // 255\n    return mask.astype(np.uint8)\n\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# MAIN PROCESSING\n# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef process_location_with_population(location, force_reprocess=False):\n    \"\"\"Process location with proper population metrics.\"\"\"\n    \n    # Check if already processed\n    output_file = os.path.join(LULC_OUTPUT_DIR, f\"{location}_results.json\")\n    if not force_reprocess and os.path.exists(output_file):\n        print(f\"⏭️ Loading existing results for {location}\")\n        with open(output_file, 'r') as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    \n    print(f\"\\n{'='*70}\")\n    print(f\"  PROCESSING: {location}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*70}\")\n    \n    # Load flood mask\n    flood_mask = load_flood_mask(location)\n    if flood_mask is None:\n        print(f\"  ❌ No flood mask found\")\n        return None\n    \n    flood_pixels = flood_mask.sum()\n    flood_area_km2 = flood_pixels * PIXEL_KM2\n    print(f\"  Flood area: {flood_area_km2:.2f} km² ({flood_pixels:,} pixels)\")\n    \n    # Get coordinates\n    lat, lon, radius_km = LOCATION_COORDS.get(location, (0, 0, 10))\n    print(f\"  Location: ({lat:.4f}, {lon:.4f})\")\n    \n    # Get georeference\n    tf, epsg = reconstruct_georeference(lat, lon, radius_km, flood_mask.shape)\n    \n    # Get or load LULC\n    lulc_npy_path = os.path.join(LULC_OUTPUT_DIR, f\"{location}_lulc_mask.npy\")\n    if os.path.exists(lulc_npy_path) and not force_reprocess:\n        lulc_mask = np.load(lulc_npy_path)\n        print(f\"  Loaded existing LULC mask\")\n    else:\n        print(\"\\n  Fetching Sentinel-2 data...\")\n        try:\n            s2_9band = fetch_s2_for_lulc(location, lat, lon, radius_km, flood_mask.shape, tf, epsg)\n            arr_14ch = compute_lulc_14ch(s2_9band)\n            print(\"  Running LULC classification...\")\n            lulc_mask = run_lulc_inference(lulc_model, arr_14ch)\n            np.save(lulc_npy_path, lulc_mask)\n            print(f\"  Saved LULC mask\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"  ❌ LULC error: {e}\")\n            return None\n    \n    # Calculate population using LULC-based estimation (reliable fallback)\n    print(\"\\n  Calculating population estimates...\")\n    pop_grid = get_estimated_population(lulc_mask)\n    \n    total_pop_scene = pop_grid.sum()\n    flooded_pixels_bool = flood_mask == 1\n    affected_population = pop_grid[flooded_pixels_bool].sum()\n    \n    print(f\"  Total population in scene: {total_pop_scene:,.0f}\")\n    print(f\"  Affected population: {affected_population:,.0f}\")\n    \n    # Calculate LULC impacts\n    flooded_lulc = lulc_mask[flooded_pixels_bool]\n    lulc_impact = {}\n    lulc_pop_impact = {}\n    \n    for class_idx, class_name in LULC_CLASS_MAP.items():\n        class_mask = (lulc_mask == class_idx)\n        class_pixels = class_mask.sum()\n        class_area_km2 = class_pixels * PIXEL_KM2\n        \n        flooded_class_pixels = ((lulc_mask == class_idx) & flooded_pixels_bool).sum()\n        flooded_class_area = flooded_class_pixels * PIXEL_KM2\n        \n        if flooded_class_area > 0:\n            lulc_impact[class_name] = round(flooded_class_area, 3)\n            \n            # Population on this LULC class that is flooded\n            pop_on_class = pop_grid[class_mask & flooded_pixels_bool].sum()\n            if pop_on_class > 0:\n                lulc_pop_impact[class_name] = int(round(pop_on_class))\n    \n    # Calculate flood percentage by class\n    flood_pct_by_class = {}\n    for class_idx, class_name in LULC_CLASS_MAP.items():\n        total_class = (lulc_mask == class_idx).sum()\n        flooded_class = ((lulc_mask == class_idx) & flooded_pixels_bool).sum()\n        if total_class > 0:\n            flood_pct_by_class[class_name] = round(100 * flooded_class / total_class, 2)\n    \n    # Compile results\n    results = {\n        \"location\": location,\n        \"lat\": lat,\n        \"lon\": lon,\n        \"radius_km\": radius_km,\n        \"total_flood_area_km2\": round(flood_area_km2, 3),\n        \"affected_population\": int(round(affected_population)),\n        \"total_population_scene\": int(round(total_pop_scene)),\n        \"population_density_per_km2\": round(total_pop_scene / (flood_mask.size * PIXEL_KM2), 1),\n        \"lulc_impact_km2\": lulc_impact,\n        \"lulc_impact_population\": lulc_pop_impact,\n        \"flood_percentage_by_class\": flood_pct_by_class,\n    }\n    \n    # Print summary\n    print(f\"\\n  ✅ RESULTS:\")\n    print(f\"     Flood area: {results['total_flood_area_km2']:.2f} km²\")\n    print(f\"     Population affected: {results['af